cs.LG, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.CV, cs.NE

The paper proposes a training algorithm for deep neural networks that optimizes the reliability of the storage separately for each layer of the network, while incurring a negligible complexity overhead compared to a conventional stochastic gradient descent training. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper deals with the energy consumption of memory elements, which suggests that it could also belong to the Architecture (cs.AR) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. The paper also mentions the use of deep neural networks in computer vision (cs.CV) and the training of binary parameters (cs.NE), which further supports the possibility of these categories.
